### Research Analysis (Cycle 6)

This cycle‚Äôs results have firmly established a focus on the practical constraints and biases introduced by tools and frameworks used in scientific reasoning, shifting from a purely philosophical understanding of 'why?' to a more critical investigation of *how* science is conducted and validated. The new search results on formal logic and software limitations highlight the influence of technical and institutional structures on the scientific process. The findings underscore that the limitations of earlier tools and practices influenced both the types of questions asked and the ways in which theories were presented and accepted. While falsifiability and logical rigor remain important, the emphasis is now on understanding the broader context within which scientific knowledge is produced, emphasizing the need to assess the impact of formalization and software on the research process.

